==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chartered
<hw>Char"tered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Granted
or established by charter; having, or existing under, a charter; having
a privilege by charter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sufficiency of <qex>chartered</qex> rights.</q>
<rj><qau>Palfrey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The air, a <qex>chartered</qex> libertine.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hired or let by charter, as a ship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Charterer</ent>⟦br⟧
